data.description: Welcome home to 349 West Chestnut Street!  When you pull up to this beautiful cape cod, you will arrive to a newly stoned driveway that you can park 2-3 cars plus have on-street parking.  As you approach the front of the house you will see the spacious covered front porch that is great for relaxing.  Upon entry of the home, you will have a freshly painted room to the left that could be used for an office or formal sitting area.      As you continue to the right, you will see the continuation of newer laminate floor which covers both front rooms.  This area makes a great dining/entertaining area and has great natural lighting with the large bay window towards the front of the house.  Transitioning to the kitchen you will find vinyl flooring, a cooktop stove with an overhead exhaust fan and mosaic backsplash.  Just from the kitchen you will find a full bath with new lighting and a first-floor bedroom.  The cozy family room has brand new vinyl flooring, crown molding, and a brick fireplace with a pellet stove.  There is a storage room next to the living room which is a perfect place for a chest freezer and other items.  A new sliding door leads outside to a great outdoor entertainment area that includes a 3-year-old 6 foot vinyl privacy fence, two deck areas and a large double door plastic shed enclosure. Heading up the steps leading to the second floor will be hardwood steps and a carpet runner.  The railings and trim recently received a fresh coat of paint.  At the top of the steps, you will find a half bath and the other two bedrooms with cubby holes and closets for lots of storage. This beauty won’t last.   Schedule your showing today!
